post_text:
WE REMEMBER 9/11

8:46 a.m. - Hijacked American Airlines Flight 11 was crashed into
the North Tower of the World Trade Center, in New York.

9:03 a.m. - Hijackers crashed United Airlines Flight 175 into the South Tower of the World Trade Center in New York.

9:37 a.m - Hijackers aboard Flight 77 crashed the plane into the Pentagon in Washington D.C.

10:07 a.m. - Flight 93 is crashed into a Pennsylvania field in Somerset County, after passengers thwarted the hijacker's attempt to target Washington D.C.

Throughout the day 2,977 people lost their lives followed by countess others as a result of related illnesses and conflicts. Let us never forget the tragic loss of life that day, the heroic actions of emergency personnel, or the resilience of the American people.

"None of us will ever forget this day, yet we go forward to defend freedom and all that is good and just in our world." - President George W. Bush

KWN News Now
August 16 at 7:59 AM ·

Just a reminder!

Isaac Miller (who has been battling leukemia) will be coming home at 1pm this afternoon, and will be escorted to his residence by our local Fire Departments, EMS, Trenton City Police Dept. and the Dade County Sherriff's Office.

We are asking people to make "Welcome Home" signs and line the streets between Trenton and Rising Fawn, to welcome this young man home.

The route will be from the interstate exit ramp in the City of Trenton, to Highway 11, South to Rising Fawn.

This was part of Isaac's "Make a Wish"!! Please come out and support him, and his recovery.

post_text:
Executive Order 07.31.20.01 extends the Public Health State of Emergency through 11:59 PM on September 10, 2020. The Public Health State of Emergency allows for enhanced coordination across government and the private sector for supply procurement, comprehensive testing, and healthcare capacity.

By renewing the applicability of existing language, Executive Order 07.31.20.02 continues to require social distancing, bans gatherings of more than fifty people unless there is six feet between each person, outlines mandatory criteria for businesses, and requires sheltering in place for those living in long-term care facilities and the medically fragile, among other provisions. The order runs through 11:59 PM on August 15, 2020.

shared_text:
Dade Health and Rehabilitation was sharing a COVID-19 Update.
June 18 at 1:37 PM ·

Family Update: All of our staff and residents are still COVID-free at this time. We continue to follow all of the measures and practices in place from the CDC and CMS and screen all essential employees before entering the building. No one is able to enter with a fever and/ or signs/ symptoms of the virus. Residents continue to participate in in-room and small group activities (with social distancing practices in place). Please don’t hesitate to call us if you would like to FaceTime or speak to your loved one on the phone. Thank you all for your patience. We can’t wait to see you all again.
